text.tspan: Do you want the results as screenshots?
If not, they are shwon on a window
Filter to smooth the heatmap (if no contours)
Filp the heatmap on the X/Y axis
Save the KDE densities as CSV files
* UI image files should have the same name as the data file but with *.png extension.
The tool reads only CSV files.
** at least 2 column names separated by spaces. No dots or other special characters: eye.x -> eyex
Example of command line generated with the UI in the image above:
python heatmap_gen.py -open C:/Projects/AnttiTraj/data/jussi -vis eyex eyey tasktime -screenshot -res 16 8 -ksize 0.3
